cs.ET, cs.AR, cs.EM, cs.DC, cs.SY

Reasoning: 
- cs.ET (Emerging Technologies): The paper proposes a new methodology for power delivery network synthesis, which can be considered an emerging technology in the field of chip design. 
- cs.AR (Architecture): The paper deals with the design of the power delivery network, which is an important aspect of chip architecture. 
- cs.EM (Electromagnetics): The paper discusses the impact of electromagnetic interference (EMI) on the power delivery network, and proposes a methodology to guard against it. 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing): The paper deals with the optimization of power delivery network over selected regions, which can be considered a form of distributed computing. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper proposes a methodology to optimize the power delivery network while ensuring power integrity, which can be considered a form of control system design.
